&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;MasterControl is looking for a motivated Account Executive to join our Quality Excellence (Qx) team. This isn&#39;t a generic software sales role; you&#39;ll be selling solutions that help life sciences and regulated-industry companies improve quality. That means Document Control, CAPA, Training Management, Audit Management, and the rest of MasterControl&#39;s quality and manufacturing excellence suite. You&#39;ll be building real relationships with quality and regulatory leaders who have serious problems to solve and showing them exactly how MasterControl helps them solve those problems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively identify and develop new business opportunities with prospective clients across regulated industries, including early-stage biotechs pursuing their first regulatory submission and established manufacturers seeking to modernize their quality management systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cultivate and maintain strong, trust-based relationships with key decision-makers and stakeholders, including Quality Directors, VPs of Regulatory Affairs, QA Managers, and executive leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop a thorough understanding of each client&#39;s quality processes, compliance challenges, and regulatory obligations, and clearly articulate how MasterControl&#39;s platform — including Document Control, CAPA, Training Management, Audit Management, and Change Control — addresses their specific needs and strengthens their overall quality posture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and deliver tailored sales presentations and product demonstrations that speak directly to the client&#39;s regulatory environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the full sales cycle — from proposal development and procurement navigation to contract negotiation and deal closure — while consistently meeting and exceeding revenue targets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate and up-to-date records of all pipeline activity, sales engagements, and account information within the CRM system.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide management with clear, consistent updates on deal progression, account health, potential risks, and resource needs to support timely and informed decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Implementation, Customer Success, and internal quality subject matter experts to facilitate a seamless customer onboarding experience and drive long-term satisfaction and retention.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a strong pulse on industry developments, including regulatory guidance updates, emerging quality trends, and the competitive landscape, leveraging that knowledge to identify new opportunities and deliver meaningful value to clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;QUALIFICATIONS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of B2B software sales experience, with a strong preference for candidates who have sold into life sciences, pharmaceutical, medical device, manufacturing, or other regulated industries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated history of consistently meeting and exceeding sales quotas in a complex, consultative sales environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience with or working knowledge of Quality Management Systems (QMS) or electronic QMS (eQMS) platforms, with a solid understanding of core quality processes including Document Control, CAPA, Training Management, Audit Management, Change Control, and Nonconformance Management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of the regulatory frameworks and quality standards applicable to regulated industries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional negotiation, presentation, and communication skills, with the ability to engage credibly with quality and regulatory professionals and effectively translate complex compliance concepts into clear business value for a variety of audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
